CandidateEmail.subject: Assessment Invitation: MBTI Personality Test
CandidateEmail.htmlBody:
Assessment Invitation

Hi Kehinde Ajayi,

Thank you for your interest in the Growth Lead position at Curacel. As part of our evaluation process, we'd like you to complete the following assessment:

MBTI Personality Test

Important Instructions

Enter your MBTI, if you know it. Should be a 4 letter word e.g ESTJ If you don't know it take the test above and take a screenshot of your result and upload

Please complete this assessment by Monday, January 12, 2026.

Start Assessment

If the button doesn't work, copy and paste this link into your browser:

https://16personalities.com

If you have any questions, please don't hesitate to reach out to us.

Best regards,
The Curacel Recruiting Team

© 2026 Curacel. All rights reserved.

This email was sent to you as part of your job application.

CoreCompetency.name: AI Tool Proficiency (Claude, Cursor, ChatGPT, etc)
Passionate Work
CoreCompetency.description: Passionate Work is at the heart of what we do. It's not just about fulfilling tasks; it's about engaging in work that truly resonates with us. This value is a blend of fun, joy and fulfillment, intertwined with a robust work ethic. When we talk about Passionate Work, we're referring to the kind of work that not only propels our business forward but also holds deep personal significance for each of us. It's this connection that drives our higher engagement, boosts our job satisfaction, and ramps up our productivity. We're not just employees; we're passionate builders, dedicated to the excellence that defines Curacel.

CoreCompetency.name: Relentless Growth
CoreCompetency.description: This value is all about embracing continuous learning and self-improvement. We're constantly seeking to broaden our skills and deepen our knowledge. This relentless pursuit of growth means we're always evolving, always moving forward. It fosters a culture brimming with curiosity and dedication to development. In the rapidly changing landscapes of tech, this isn't just beneficial; it's essential. We're committed to staying ahead of the curve, ensuring that as individuals and as a company, we're not just keeping pace, but setting the pace.

CoreCompetency.name: Empowered Action
CoreCompetency.description: This value is about more than just doing; it's about taking initiative and owning our decisions. As an Exceller, I'm part of a culture where every team member is not just allowed, but encouraged, to step up and lead. We're given the autonomy to own our projects and the responsibility that comes with it. This isn't just empowering on a personal level; it transforms how we function as an organization. We become agile, responsive, and proactive. Empowered Action means we're not waiting for directions; we're creating paths, making informed decisions, and driving Curacel forward with confidence and accountability.

CoreCompetency.name: Sense of Urgency
CoreCompetency.description: This value is about recognizing the importance of speed and responsiveness in everything we do. As an Exceller, I understand that being proactive in addressing challenges and seizing opportunities is crucial. We're not just responding to the market; we're anticipating and shaping it. This urgency is not about rushing through tasks; it's about understanding the pace of our industry and the need to stay ahead. It's what keeps us competitive, allowing us to quickly capitalize on emerging trends and adapt to changes. Our Sense of Urgency ensures that we are always a step ahead, ready to turn ideas into action and possibilities into realities.

CoreCompetency.name: Seeing Possibilities
CoreCompetency.description: It's about maintaining a perspective that is always geared towards solutions and opportunities, rather than being bogged down by limitations. As an Exceller, I am constantly inspired to approach every situation with an innovative mindset. This value isn't just about optimism; it's about a proactive willingness to explore new ideas and avenues. It's crucial, especially in emerging markets where the landscape is constantly evolving and traditional methods might not always apply. Seeing Possibilities drives us to think outside the box, to be open to unconventional approaches, and to view every challenge as a stepping stone to breakthroughs and success. It's this value that empowers us to not only navigate but also shape the future of our industry.

JobDescription.name: Senior Backend Engineer
JobDescription.content:
# Senior Backend Engineer

## About the Role
We're looking for a Senior Backend Engineer to join our growing engineering team. You'll be responsible for designing, building, and maintaining our core platform services.

## Responsibilities
- Design and implement scalable backend services and APIs
- Lead technical discussions and code reviews
- Mentor junior engineers and contribute to team growth
- Collaborate with product and design teams to deliver features
- Ensure high code quality through testing and best practices
- Participate in on-call rotations

## Requirements
- 5+ years of backend development experience
- Strong proficiency in Node.js, Python, or Go
- Experience with PostgreSQL, Redis, and message queues
- Understanding of distributed systems and microservices
- Excellent problem-solving and communication skills

## Nice to Have
- Experience with Kubernetes and cloud platforms (AWS/GCP)
- Contributions to open source projects
- Experience in fintech or insurtech

JobDescription.name: Product Designer
JobDescription.content:
# Product Designer

## About the Role
We're seeking a talented Product Designer to help shape the future of our platform. You'll work closely with product and engineering teams to create intuitive, beautiful user experiences.

## Responsibilities
- Lead end-to-end design for new features and products

JobDescription.name: DevOps Engineer

# DevOps Engineer

## About the Role
We're seeking a DevOps Engineer to help build and maintain our cloud infrastructure. You'll work on CI/CD pipelines, monitoring, and ensuring system reliability.

## Responsibilities
- Design and maintain cloud infrastructure on AWS/GCP
- Build and optimize CI/CD pipelines
- Implement monitoring, alerting, and logging solutions

JobDescription.name: Growth Lead
JobDescription.content:
Your Objective

Youâ€™re a dynamic Growth Marketing Leader, who will be responsible for crafting and executing a comprehensive marketing strategy. This includes overseeing various marketing domains such as product marketing, performance marketing, events, social media marketing, and partnerships.

How you'll help us achieve it

  • Develop and oversee the company's growth strategy in collaboration with Curacel's Management Team.

  • Establish a robust growth and marketing division within Curacel

  • Regularly report and forecast crucial business metrics, including customer growth, retention, revenue, engagement, NPS, and profit margins.

  • Innovate in user acquisition, targeting the first major milestones of customers.

  • Gain an in-depth understanding of our current and potential users and their motivations.

  • Master our customer acquisition channels, marketing funnels, and tools.

  • Manage the marketing budget effectively across various tools and channels.

  • Lead growth experimentation, optimising existing channels and exploring new opportunities.

  • Champion a data-driven culture, emphasising instrumentation and attribution.

  • Work closely with the Product Team to refine user experience, copy, and messaging.

  • Maintain and develop the Curacel brand and voice, ensuring consistency across all communications.

  • Lead and expand the Growth/Marketing Team.

In your first month, you'll

  • Learn what we do, how our product works and what new products we are building.

  • Build a structure for monitoring progress and measuring the success of campaigns and marketing activities.

  • Gain an in-depth understanding of our current and potential users and their motivations.

  • Review existing content calendar and create a new one for our social media, newsletter and blog.

  • Lead the creation of reports and white papers for insurance, claims management, fraud detection, embedded insurance in Africa.

  • Lead the creation of video testimonials of our clients across Africa.

Requirements

  • Minimum of 6 years of experience in B2B Marketing, with a focus on both small and medium-sized businesses, SEO and growth marketing.

  • Proficient in marketing analytics and applying insights to optimise campaigns.

  • Demonstrated ability in being analytical and data-driven.

  • Strong leadership skills, with the ability to work with cross-functional teams.

  • Proven track record of growth, with examples and outcomes of previous campaigns.

  • Exceptional written, oral, and organisational skills.

  • Experience in managing comprehensive, data-driven marketing, and communication strategies.

  • Familiarity with relevant marketing tools and platforms for campaign activation.

Bonus points if you

  • Have B2B SaaS marketing experience

Key details

  • The growth marketing position is a full-time position and reports to the CEO.

Benefits:

  • Subsidized health insurance

  • Monthly data allowance

JobDescription.name: GTM Engineer
JobDescription.content:
Overview

Curacel is a leading African insurtech company using AI, data, and modern software to transform insurance infrastructure across the continent. We partner with insurers, brokers, and healthcare providers to eliminate fraud, improve efficiency, and create seamless insurance experiences at scale. As a GTM (Go-To-Market) Engineer in the Commercial team, you will sit at the intersection of product, engineering, sales, and marketing. Your role is to design, build, and optimize the technical and operational systems that power Curacelâ€™s revenue growthâ€”from lead acquisition and onboarding to integrations, pricing experiments, and customer expansion. This role matters because Curacelâ€™s growth depends not just on great products, but on how efficiently and intelligently we take them to market. You will directly impact revenue velocity, customer experience, and scalability, enabling Curacel to grow faster and smarter across multiple markets.

Key Responsibilities

  • Design, implement, and maintain GTM systems and tooling that support sales, partnerships, and customer success (CRM, automation, analytics, integrations).
  • Work closely with Sales, Marketing, Product, and Engineering teams to translate commercial needs into scalable technical solutions.
  • Build and optimize workflows for lead management, onboarding, pricing, and customer lifecycle management.
  • Develop dashboards and reporting frameworks to track funnel performance, revenue metrics, and GTM efficiency.
  • Support pre-sales and post-sales technical engagements, including demos, integrations, and solution design for enterprise customers.
  • Identify bottlenecks in the go-to-market process and proactively design experiments and improvements.
  • Own documentation and knowledge-sharing around GTM systems, processes, and best practices.
  • Continuously evaluate and recommend new tools, technologies, and processes to improve speed, accuracy, and impact.

Required Qualifications

  • 3â€“6 years of experience in GTM Engineering, Sales Engineering, Revenue Operations, Growth Engineering, or a similar role.
  • Strong technical foundation with experience in APIs, system integrations, automation tools, and data workflows.
  • Hands-on experience with CRM platforms (e.g., HubSpot, Salesforce) and sales/marketing automation tools.
  • Ability to analyze data, build dashboards, and derive actionable insights to support commercial decisions.
  • Strong problem-solving skills with a bias for ownership, experimentation, and execution.
  • Excellent communication skills and ability to work cross-functionally with technical and non-technical stakeholders.
  • Bachelorâ€™s degree in Engineering, Computer Science, Information Systems, or a related field (or equivalent practical experience).

Preferred Qualifications

  • Experience working in a high-growth startup or scale-up environment, preferably in SaaS or fintech/insurtech.
  • Familiarity with data tools such as SQL, Python, or modern BI platforms.
  • Experience supporting enterprise or B2B sales cycles in emerging markets.
  • Understanding of insurance, healthcare, or financial services ecosystems in Africa.
  • Experience designing pricing experiments, revenue models, or growth experiments.

Benefits & Perks

  • Competitive salary and performance-based incentives.
  • Opportunity to work on high-impact products transforming insurance across Africa.
  • Fast-paced, ownership-driven culture aligned with Curacelâ€™s PRESS values.
  • Clear growth paths, learning opportunities, and exposure to leadership.
  • Flexible work environment with a strong focus on outcomes over hours.
  • Collaborative, innovative team that values initiative, urgency, and creativity.

About Curacel

Curacelâ€™s mission is to make insurance workâ€”better, faster, and more transparentlyâ€”for everyone. We leverage AI, automation, and data to combat fraud, streamline claims, and modernize insurance operations across Africa. Our culture is built around our PRESS values: Passionate Work, Relentless Growth, Empowered Action, Sense of Urgency, and Seeing Possibilities. We believe in giving our people ownership, trusting them to make decisions, and supporting them to grow. At Curacel, your work has real impact. Every system you build, process you improve, and customer you enable helps strengthen insurance infrastructure and expand access to financial protection across the continent.

JobDescription.name: AI/ML Engineer
JobDescription.content:
Overview

Curacel is a leading African insurtech company building the digital infrastructure that powers insurance operations across the continent. Through cutting-edge AI, data, and automation, we help insurers reduce fraud, improve claims processing, and deliver better experiences to millions of customers. At Curacel, we move fast, take ownership, and build products that solve real, high-impact problems. As an AI/ML Engineer, you will play a critical role in designing, building, and deploying machine learning models that sit at the core of our products. You will work on real-world challenges such as fraud detection, claims automation, risk scoring, and intelligent decision systems, transforming raw data into scalable, production-ready AI solutions. This role matters because AI is central to Curacelâ€™s mission. Your work will directly influence product performance, customer trust, and business outcomes across multiple insurance partners. You will help shape how AI is applied responsibly and effectively in one of Africaâ€™s most impactful fintech sectors.

Key Responsibilities

  • Design, develop, train, and deploy machine learning models for production use cases such as fraud detection, claims automation, and predictive analytics
  • Collaborate closely with product managers, backend engineers, and data analysts to translate business problems into scalable AI/ML solutions
  • Build and maintain end-to-end ML pipelines, including data preprocessing, model training, evaluation, deployment, and monitoring
  • Continuously improve model performance through experimentation, feature engineering, and model optimization
  • Ensure models are reliable, explainable, and production-ready, with proper monitoring and retraining strategies
  • Work with large, complex datasets and ensure data quality, integrity, and security
  • Document models, processes, and experiments to support knowledge sharing and long-term maintainability

Required Qualifications

  • 3+ years of hands-on experience building and deploying machine learning models in a production environment
  • Strong proficiency in Python and common ML libraries such as TensorFlow, PyTorch, Scikit-learn, or similar
  • Solid understanding of machine learning fundamentals, including supervised and unsupervised learning, model evaluation, and feature engineering
  • Experience working with structured and unstructured data, including data cleaning and preprocessing
  • Familiarity with APIs, microservices, and integrating ML models into backend systems
  • Experience with cloud platforms (AWS, GCP, or Azure) and ML deployment workflows
  • Bachelorâ€™s degree in Computer Science, Engineering, Data Science, or a related field (or equivalent practical experience)

Preferred Qualifications

  • Experience with MLOps tools and practices such as model versioning, CI/CD for ML, and model monitoring
  • Knowledge of fraud detection, risk modeling, or financial services use cases
  • Experience working with big data tools or data warehouses
  • Familiarity with NLP, computer vision, or deep learning applications
  • Experience working in a fast-paced startup or scale-up environment
  • Advanced degree (Masterâ€™s or PhD) in a relevant field

Benefits & Perks

  • Opportunity to work on high-impact, real-world AI problems affecting millions of users across Africa
  • A culture of ownership, innovation, and empowered decision-making aligned with Curacelâ€™s PRESS values
  • Competitive compensation and performance-based growth opportunities
  • Collaborative, fast-paced work environment with talented engineers and product leaders
  • Learning and development support, including exposure to modern AI tools and production systems
  • Flexible work arrangements and a results-driven culture

About Curacel

Curacelâ€™s mission is to make insurance work better for everyone by building the digital infrastructure that insurers need to operate efficiently and transparently. We envision an Africa where insurance is trusted, accessible, and powered by intelligent technology. Our culture is guided by our PRESS values: Passionate Work, Relentless Growth, Empowered Action, Sense of Urgency, and Seeing Possibilities. We believe in moving fast, taking ownership, and continuously learning. By partnering with leading insurers and leveraging AI at scale, Curacel is transforming how claims are processed, how fraud is detected, and how trust is built in insurance systems across the continent. Joining Curacel means being part of a team creating meaningful impact at the intersection of technology and financial inclusion.

Curacel Systems Limited (the "Company"), a company incorporated under the laws of the Federal Republic of Nigeria, having its office at 19 Adeyemi Lawson Street, Ikoyi, Lagos, is pleased to employ you under the following terms and conditions (the "Agreement"):

You cannot accumulate and carry over your annual leave entitlement from one year to the following year. If you are unable to work as a result of ill health or injury, you shall notify the Company by providing a medical certificate setting out the reasons for absence from work. You shall be able to access seven (7) business days of sick leave within a year.

Should it become necessary, you are entitled to maternity leave for a period of three (3) consecutive months commencing at any time before the expected delivery date or as directed by a medical practitioner. You shall however notify the Company at least four (4) weeks before you intend taking the maternity leave.

Disciplinary and Grievance Procedure: You shall be subject to the disciplinary and grievance procedures as provided in the Company's employee handbook from time to time.

Confidentiality and Invention/ Intellectual Property Assignment Agreement: You will be required, as a condition of your employment with the Company, to sign the Company's standard Confidentiality and Invention/Intellectual Property Assignment Agreement provided in Appendix II of this Agreement.

Termination of Employment and Notice Period: This Agreement may be terminated by:

Death

Disabilities, which include any physical or mental impairment which, as reasonably determined by the Company, renders you unable to perform the essential functions of your position at the Company

With or Without Cause.

Notwithstanding the above should you wish to terminate this Agreement during the Probation Period, one (1) month's notice in writing must be given to the Company. Salary may be paid or forfeited in lieu of notice. After your Confirmation, should either Party wish to terminate this relationship, one (1) month's notice in writing must be given to the non-terminating Party. Salary may be paid or forfeited in lieu of notice by either Party. This notice period is deemed necessary as it is pertinent that you do a proper handover and annual leave periods will not be accepted as part of the notice period.

Please note that payment in lieu of notice will only be accepted following approval from your line manager that you have concluded assigned tasks and done proper handover.

Nothing in this Agreement shall prevent the Company from terminating your employment without notice or salary in lieu of notice in the appropriate circumstances including:

any material breach by you of this Agreement, the Confidential Information Non-Disclosure & Intellectual Property/ Invention Assignment Agreement between you and the Company, or any other written agreement between you and the Company, if such breach causes material harm to the Company;

any material failure by you to comply with the Company's written policies or rules, as they may be in effect from time to time during your Employment, if such failure causes material harm to the Company;

any conviction of, or a plea of "guilty" to a crime under the laws of the Federal Republic of Nigeria or any other country;

your misappropriation of funds or property of the Company;

neglect of your duties;

or any gross or wilful misconduct by you resulting in a material loss to the Company or material damage to the reputation of the Company.

Restrictive Covenants: While employed by the Company and for 12 months after the termination of your employment, you shall not seek to:

Canvass or solicit business, orders or custom for any products or services provided by this business from any customer, supplier or sponsor; either current, existing or in prospect;

Solicit or entice away any of the Company's employees or contract employees

Transfer your services to the Company's customer, supplier or sponsor.

Employment Relationship: Employment with the Company is for no specific period of time. Your employment with the Company will be "at will," meaning that either you or the Company may terminate your employment at any time and for any reason, with or without cause. Any contrary representations which may have been made to you are superseded by this offer. This is the full and complete agreement between you and the Company regarding this issue. Although your job duties, title, compensation and benefits, as well as the Company's personnel policies and procedures, may change from time to time, the "at will" nature of your employment may only be changed in an express written agreement signed by you and the Company's Managing Director.

Conflicting Employment: You hereby agree that, during the duration of this Agreement you shall be committed to carrying out your duties in the Company and will not engage in any other employment (Full-time or Part-time), occupation, consulting, or other business activity nor will you engage in any other activities that conflict with your obligations to the Company without the prior written consent of the Company.

Loss, Damage and Return of Company Property: The Company shall not accept any responsibility for the loss or damage of your personal property, motor vehicle and/or any other personal belongings brought into the Company's premises in the course of your employment. Upon termination of employment with the Company for any reason or at any time prior at the Company's request, you shall return all property belonging to the Company or its affiliates including but not limited to, any Company-provided laptops, computers, cell phones, or other equipment, or documents, or property belonging to the Company.

Governing Law: The validity, interpretation, construction and performance of this Agreement, and all acts and transactions pursuant to this Agreement and the rights and obligations of the parties hereto shall be governed, construed and interpreted in accordance with the Laws of the Federal Republic of Nigeria.

Entire Agreement: This Agreement contains the entire Agreement between the parties hereto with respect to the subject matter hereof, and supersedes all prior arrangements or understandings (whether written or oral) with respect thereto.

Severability: If any provision in this Agreement is held to be invalid or unenforceable in any jurisdiction, the validity and enforceability of all remaining provisions contained in this Agreement shall not in any way be affected or impaired.

We reserve the right to make reasonable changes to this Agreement and will notify you in writing of such changes. Such changes will be deemed to be accepted unless you notify us of any objections you may have before the commencement date. By signing this Agreement, you confirm with the Company that you are under no contractual or other legal obligations that would prohibit you from performing your duties with the Company.

If you wish to accept this offer, please sign and date both copies of this Agreement and both copies of the enclosed Confidential Information and Intellectual Property/Invention Assignment Agreement on or before 2025-12-26 and return them to the undersigned representative of the Company.

Transfer your services to the Company's customer, supplier or sponsor.

Commencement Date: %{employment_start_date}

Position: For the period of your employment under this Agreement, the Company agrees to employ you in the position of %{job_title}. You will report to the %{supervisor_title} or to such other person as the Company subsequently may determine.

Place of Work: The Company's primary location is at 16, Oyekan Road, Surulere, Lagos, Nigeria, where you will be expected to provide the Services twice/thrice a week. However you may be expected to provide the Services remotely or at any other place determined by the Company.

Death

Disabilities, which include any physical or mental impairment which, as reasonably determined by the Company, renders you unable to perform the essential functions of your position at the Company

your misappropriation of funds or property of the Company;

neglect of your duties;

or any gross or wilful misconduct by you resulting in a material loss to the Company or material damage to the reputation of the Company.

Canvass or solicit business, orders or custom for any products or services provided by this business from any customer, supplier or sponsor; either current, existing or in prospect;

Solicit or entice away any of the Company's employees or contract employees

Transfer your services to the Company's customer, supplier or sponsor.

Although your job duties, title, compensation and benefits, as well as the Company's personnel policies and procedures, may change from time to time, the "at will" nature of your employment may only be changed in an express written agreement signed by you and the Company's Managing Director.

Conflicting Employment: You hereby agree that, during the duration of this Agreement you shall be committed to carrying out your duties in the Company and will not engage in any other employment (Part-time or Part-time), occupation, consulting, or other business activity nor will you engage in any other activities that conflict with your obligations to the Company without the prior written consent of the Company.

Loss, Damage and Return of Company Property: The Company shall not accept any responsibility for the loss or damage of your personal property, motor vehicle and/or any other personal belongings brought into the Company's premises in the course of your employment. Upon termination of employment with the Company for any reason or at any time prior at the Company's request, you shall return all property belonging to the Company or its affiliates including but not limited to, any Company-provided laptops, computers, cell phones, or other equipment, or documents, or property belonging to the Company.

Governing Law: The validity, interpretation, construction and performance of this Agreement, and all acts and transactions pursuant to this Agreement and the rights and obligations of the parties hereto shall be governed, construed and interpreted in accordance with the Laws of the Federal Republic of Nigeria.

Entire Agreement: This Agreement contains the entire Agreement between the parties hereto with respect to the subject matter hereof, and supersedes all prior arrangements or understandings (whether written or oral) with respect thereto.

Severability: If any provision in this Agreement is held to be invalid or unenforceable in any jurisdiction, the validity and enforceability of all remaining provisions contained in this Agreement shall not in any way be affected or impaired.

We reserve the right to make reasonable changes to this Agreement and will notify you in writing of such changes. Such changes will be deemed to be accepted unless you notify us of any objections you may have before the commencement date. By signing this Agreement, you confirm with the Company that you are under no contractual or other legal obligations that would prohibit you from performing your duties with the Company.

If you wish to accept this offer, please sign and date both copies of this Agreement and both copies of the enclosed Confidential Information and Intellectual Property/Invention Assignment Agreement on or before %{offer_expiration_date} and return them to the undersigned representative of the Company.

OfferTemplate.name: BYOD Agreement
OfferTemplate.description: Bring Your Own Device undertaking form for employees using personal devices for work
OfferTemplate.bodyHtml:
BRING YOUR OWN DEVICE (BYOD) UNDERTAKING FORM

I, {{employee_name}}, working in the {{department}} department as {{job_title}}, hereby acknowledge that I will be using my personal device(s) for official company work purposes.

Device Information

Device Model/Name {{device_model}}
Product Serial Number {{serial_number}}
Charger Serial Number {{charger_serial}}
IMEI Number (if applicable) {{imei_number}}

Terms and Conditions

By signing this undertaking, I agree to the following:

  1. IT Access: I understand that the Company's IT department may need access to my device for security configuration, software installation, or troubleshooting purposes related to company work.
  2. Data Responsibility: I acknowledge that I am responsible for maintaining the security of company data stored on or accessed through my personal device. I will use appropriate security measures including but not limited to password protection, encryption, and keeping software up to date.
  3. Acceptable Use: I will use my device in accordance with the Company's IT policies and acceptable use guidelines. I will not install or use software that may compromise company security or data.
  4. Data Separation: I understand that company data should be kept separate from personal data where possible, and I will follow company guidelines for data handling and storage.
  5. Loss or Theft: I will immediately report any loss, theft, or security breach involving my device to the IT department and my manager.
  6. Exit Procedures: Upon termination of employment, I agree to allow the IT department to remove all company data, applications, and access credentials from my device.
  7. No Company Liability: I understand that the Company is not responsible for loss, damage, or theft of my personal device, nor for any personal data stored on my device.
  8. Compliance: I agree to comply with all applicable data protection laws and regulations when handling company data on my personal device.

Acknowledgment

I have read and understood this BYOD Undertaking Form. I agree to abide by all terms and conditions outlined above and any related company policies regarding the use of personal devices for work purposes.

I acknowledge that failure to comply with these terms may result in disciplinary action, up to and including termination of employment.

Employee Signature:

{{employee_name}}

Date:

{{signature_date}}

Scorecard.mission: Design, implement, and optimize scalable go-to-market systems that enable the Commercial team to efficiently acquire, convert, and retain customers while driving predictable revenue growth.

outcomes.name: GTM Infrastructure Buildout
outcomes.description: Develop and maintain the technical and operational infrastructure that supports go-to-market motions across sales, marketing, and customer success.
successCriteria: Core GTM tools (CRM, marketing automation, data stack) are implemented and fully operational
Automations reduce manual GTM workflows by at least 30%
Documentation exists for all core GTM systems and processes

outcomes.name: Revenue Process Optimization
outcomes.description: Improve end-to-end revenue processes to increase conversion rates, shorten sales cycles, and reduce friction across the funnel.
successCriteria: Sales cycle length reduced by a measurable percentage (e.g., 10â€“20%)
Lead-to-opportunity and opportunity-to-close conversion rates improve quarter-over-quarter
Clear, standardized handoffs exist between Marketing, Sales, and Customer Success

outcomes.name: Data & Insights Enablement
outcomes.description: Ensure the Commercial team has access to accurate, actionable data to guide decision-making and performance management.
successCriteria: Dashboards are live for funnel performance, pipeline health, and revenue forecasting
Data accuracy across GTM systems exceeds 95%
Commercial leaders regularly use dashboards in planning and reviews

outcomes.name: Experimentation & Growth Enablement
outcomes.description: Enable rapid experimentation of GTM strategies, messaging, and channels to identify and scale what drives growth.
successCriteria: At least 1â€“2 GTM experiments launched per month
Clear experiment results documented with learnings and next steps
Successful experiments are operationalized and scaled within a defined timeframe

Scorecard.mission: Enable a positive, compliant, and efficient employee experience by supporting core People Operations processes and ensuring employees and managers are well-supported throughout the employee lifecycle.

outcomes.name: Employee Lifecycle Operations
outcomes.description: Ensure smooth and timely execution of employee lifecycle processes including onboarding, offboarding, and employee changes.
successCriteria: 100% of new hires complete onboarding within their first week
All employee changes (role, compensation, status) are processed within 2 business days
Offboarding tasks are completed within defined timelines for 95%+ of exits

outcomes.name: Employee Experience & Support
outcomes.description: Provide responsive, accurate, and empathetic support to employee questions and requests related to People policies, benefits, and tools.
successCriteria: Respond to employee PeopleOps inquiries within 1 business day on average
Maintain a 90%+ employee satisfaction score on PeopleOps support interactions
Reduce repeat inquiries by maintaining up-to-date FAQs or documentation

outcomes.name: HR Compliance & Data Accuracy
outcomes.description: Maintain accurate employee records and support compliance with labor laws, company policies, and internal controls.
successCriteria: Maintain 99%+ accuracy across HRIS employee data audits
All required employee documentation is completed and stored on time
Zero missed compliance deadlines related to employment documentation

outcomes.name: People Systems & Process Improvement
outcomes.description: Support and continuously improve PeopleOps systems and processes to increase efficiency and scalability.
successCriteria: Identify and implement at least 1â€“2 process improvements per quarter
Reduce manual PeopleOps tasks or processing time by at least 10%
Ensure accurate and timely data entry across all People systems

Scorecard.mission: Design, build, and deploy reliable AI/ML solutions that deliver measurable business impact while maintaining high standards of performance, scalability, and responsible AI practices.

outcomes.name: Production-Ready ML Solutions
outcomes.description: Develop and deploy machine learning models that are robust, scalable, and integrated into production systems to solve real business problems.
successCriteria: At least 2â€“3 ML models deployed to production per year supporting core business use cases
Models meet or exceed agreed performance benchmarks (e.g., accuracy, precision/recall, RMSE)
Production incidents related to ML systems remain below an agreed threshold (e.g., <2 critical incidents per quarter)

outcomes.name: Model Performance & Optimization
outcomes.description: Continuously evaluate, monitor, and improve model performance to ensure sustained value and reliability over time.
successCriteria: Model performance metrics are monitored with automated dashboards and alerts in place
Performance degradation is detected and addressed within defined SLAs
At least one measurable improvement cycle (e.g., retraining, feature enhancement) completed per model per quarter

outcomes.name: Data & Feature Engineering Excellence
outcomes.description: Build high-quality data pipelines and feature engineering processes that enable accurate, repeatable, and explainable ML models.
successCriteria: Data pipelines achieve agreed reliability targets (e.g., >99% successful scheduled runs)
Key features are documented, versioned, and reusable across models
Data quality issues are identified and resolved within defined timelines

outcomes.name: Collaboration & Knowledge Sharing
outcomes.description: Work effectively with cross-functional teams and contribute to a strong AI/ML engineering culture through documentation and knowledge sharing.
successCriteria: Regular collaboration with product, engineering, and data teams resulting in clearly defined ML requirements
Clear technical documentation created for all production ML systems
Active participation in design reviews, code reviews, or internal knowledge-sharing sessions each quarter

SubCompetency.name: Enjoyment
SubCompetency.description: You find genuine satisfaction and joy in your work, seeing it not just as a task but as a meaningful part of your life. This means approaching every project with enthusiasm, which reflects in the positivity and creativity you bring to the team and your work.

levelDescriptions.1: You appreciate the idea of finding joy in your work but often need guidance to see the enjoyable aspects of your tasks.
levelDescriptions.2: You start to identify aspects of your work that you enjoy and seek tasks that align with these interests, with occasional encouragement.
levelDescriptions.3: You consistently find joy in your work, making it a point to engage in tasks that resonate with your interests and strengths.
levelDescriptions.4: You not only derive deep satisfaction from your work but also inspire your colleagues to find enjoyment in their tasks, enhancing overall team morale.
levelDescriptions.5: You cultivate a workplace culture that values enjoyment in work, leading initiatives that help everyone find passion in their responsibilities.

SubCompetency.name: Drive
SubCompetency.description: You possess an intrinsic motivation that fuels your commitment to your work and the goals of Curacel. This means setting ambitious targets for yourself and tirelessly pursuing them, showing resilience and determination in the face of challenges.

levelDescriptions.1: You show initial motivation towards tasks but often require external motivation to sustain effort over time.
levelDescriptions.2: You demonstrate more consistent motivation and are beginning to set personal goals, though you sometimes need reminders or support to stay on track.
levelDescriptions.3: Your drive is self-sustaining; you set and pursue ambitious goals independently and are resilient in the face of obstacles.
levelDescriptions.4: Your high level of motivation serves as a model for others; you mentor colleagues in goal setting and perseverance.
levelDescriptions.5: You are a key driver in fostering a highly motivated workplace, implementing strategies that enhance organizational drive and ambition.

SubCompetency.name: Exceed Expectations
SubCompetency.description: You consistently go above and beyond what is required, aiming to surpass the set standards in every task you undertake. This means not just meeting deadlines but delivering work that sets a new benchmark for excellence, contributing significantly to Curacel's success.

levelDescriptions.1: You understand the importance of meeting expectations but require guidance to understand what exceeding them entails.
levelDescriptions.2: You occasionally go beyond the basic requirements of tasks with some oversight, showing an understanding of what it means to exceed expectations.
levelDescriptions.3: You consistently deliver work that surpasses requirements without needing external prompts, showcasing high standards and attention to detail.
levelDescriptions.4: You not only exceed expectations in your own work but also guide your peers in doing so, raising the bar for your team's performance.
levelDescriptions.5: You lead by example and set new benchmarks for excellence within Curacel, shaping policies or practices that encourage everyone to exceed expectations.

SubCompetency.name: Curiosity
SubCompetency.description: You possess a deep-seated desire to learn and discover new things, constantly questioning the status quo and seeking out new knowledge and skills. This means being open to new ideas and approaches, always looking for ways to improve both personally and professionally.

levelDescriptions.1: You show initial interest in new information and experiences but rely on external prompts to explore further.
levelDescriptions.2: You actively seek out learning opportunities within known boundaries and is more open to challenges, though sometimes dependent on guidance.
levelDescriptions.3: You independently explore new areas of knowledge, apply learning to work, and is self-driven in overcoming challenges.
levelDescriptions.4: You serve as a role model for continuous learning and problem-solving, encouraging and guiding others in their curiosity journeys.
levelDescriptions.5: You lead organizational learning initiatives, creating a culture that values and promotes curiosity and continuous improvement.

SubCompetency.name: Ambitious Goals
SubCompetency.description: You set high, challenging objectives for yourself and the team, pushing the boundaries of what's considered achievable. This means not being content with mediocrity but striving for significant achievements that contribute to Curacel's overarching mission.

levelDescriptions.1: You recognize the importance of goals but need help to set and pursue them effectively.
levelDescriptions.2: You set personal goals with some ambition and pursue them with encouragement, showing progress in challenging oneself.
levelDescriptions.3: You regularly set and achieve high goals independently, demonstrating a strong drive and commitment to personal and professional growth.
levelDescriptions.4: You inspire and assist others in setting and reaching ambitious goals, contributing to a high-performing team environment.
levelDescriptions.5: You shape the goal-setting culture of Curacel, developing frameworks that encourage ambitious goal-setting and achievement across the organization.

SubCompetency.name: Adaptable Mindset
SubCompetency.description: You demonstrate a high level of flexibility and resilience in the face of change, viewing obstacles as opportunities to grow and innovate. This means being able to pivot strategies, learn from setbacks, and continue moving forward with a positive outlook, ensuring sustained growth and progress.

levelDescriptions.1: You understand the concept of adaptability but struggle to adjust to change without guidance.
levelDescriptions.2: You shows flexibility in familiar situations and is learning to adjust strategies based on feedback, with some reliance on support.
levelDescriptions.3: You demonstrate resilience and flexibility across a range of scenarios, independently adapting to new challenges and changes.
levelDescriptions.4: You act as a change champion within teams, helping others to navigate and adapt to new situations effectively.
levelDescriptions.5: You lead organizational change initiatives, fostering a culture that embraces adaptability, resilience, and innovation at all levels.

SubCompetency.name: Ownership
SubCompetency.description: You take full responsibility for your tasks and projects, treating them as if they were your own business, demonstrating a strong commitment to the team's success. This means being accountable for the outcomes, proactively addressing issues, and ensuring that every aspect of your work is executed to the highest standard.

levelDescriptions.1: You acknowledge responsibility for tasks but often require direction and follow-up to ensure accountability.
levelDescriptions.2: You take responsibility for tasks and shows some proactive problem-solving, though occasionally needs encouragement to fully own projects.
levelDescriptions.3: You fully own projects and outcomes, proactively addressing challenges and taking responsibility for results without external prompts.
levelDescriptions.4: You empower others to take ownership, providing guidance and support to foster accountability and responsibility in the team.
levelDescriptions.5: You cultivate a strong sense of ownership across Curacel, embedding accountability and self-driven responsibility into the organizational culture.

SubCompetency.name: Initiative
SubCompetency.description: You are proactive, not waiting for directions to act. You identify opportunities for improvement and take the lead in implementing solutions. This means consistently looking for ways to contribute beyond your usual responsibilities and being a driving force for positive change within Curacel.

levelDescriptions.1: You show willingness to take on tasks but often wait for instructions before acting.
levelDescriptions.2: You begin to act on opportunities within a defined scope and is more proactive, though sometimes hesitate without clear direction.
levelDescriptions.3: You regularly seek out and act on opportunities for improvement and innovation, demonstrating a high level of proactivity and independence.
levelDescriptions.4: You lead by example in taking initiative, mentoring others to be proactive, and identifying and seizing opportunities.
levelDescriptions.5: You shape the organizational culture to prioritize and value initiative, implementing systems that encourage and reward proactive behavior.

SubCompetency.name: Communication
SubCompetency.description: You actively and respectfully engage in the exchange of ideas, expectations, and feedback, ensuring transparency and clarity in all interactions. Without prompt, you regularly provide updates and progress reports on your tasks, fostering a culture of openness and accountability. You place a high value on the contributions and perspectives of every team member, recognizing the importance of diverse viewpoints and collaborative synergy in achieving Curacel's goals.

levelDescriptions.1: You understand basic communication principles but may struggle to convey or receive messages clearly without assistance.
levelDescriptions.2: You communicate effectively in familiar contexts and is developing skills for more effective team and client interactions, with occasional support needed.
levelDescriptions.3: You excel in clear and effective communication across a variety of contexts, ensuring alignment and understanding within teams and with clients.
levelDescriptions.4: You act as a communication role model, coaching others in effective communication strategies and fostering an environment of open and constructive dialogue.
levelDescriptions.5: You lead the development and implementation of communication standards and practices at Curacel, enhancing organizational clarity, collaboration, and efficiency.

SubCompetency.name: Expediency
SubCompetency.description: You approach your work with a swift and efficient manner, understanding that time is of the essence in achieving Curacel's objectives. This means consistently looking for the most effective ways to accomplish tasks, ensuring that results are delivered not just on time, but as promptly as possible without compromising quality.

levelDescriptions.1: You recognize the need for timely action but may not consistently deliver results quickly without reminders.
levelDescriptions.2: You begin to complete tasks more promptly, showing an improving pace in work with some oversight needed for timely delivery.
levelDescriptions.3: You consistently meet or exceed time-sensitive goals, efficiently managing tasks and deadlines without compromising quality.
levelDescriptions.4: You drive team efficiency, helping others improve their work pace and meeting critical deadlines effectively.
levelDescriptions.5: You establishe standards and processes that enhance organizational efficiency, ensuring a high sense of urgency is maintained across all teams.

SubCompetency.name: Agility
SubCompetency.description: You exhibit flexibility and responsiveness to changes and new demands, adapting quickly to shifting priorities and market conditions. This means being able to adjust your strategies and actions on the fly, ensuring that Curacel remains competitive and responsive to opportunities and challenges.

levelDescriptions.1: You show awareness of the need for flexibility but struggle to adapt to new directions or unexpected changes without guidance.
levelDescriptions.2: You adapt to changes within known scenarios with some ease, though may require support in more complex situations.
levelDescriptions.3: You demonstrate strong adaptability, quickly adjusting to new information, challenges, and shifting priorities independently.
levelDescriptions.4: You guide and support others in becoming more agile, facilitating a nimble response to change within the team.
levelDescriptions.5: You lead the development of an agile organizational culture, embedding flexibility and responsiveness into Curacel's operational DNA.

SubCompetency.name: Prioritization
SubCompetency.description: You effectively identify the most critical tasks and challenges that align with Curacel's strategic goals, focusing your energy and resources on what matters most. This means making informed decisions about where to allocate your time and effort, ensuring that high-impact activities are addressed with the urgency they require.

levelDescriptions.1: You understand the concept of prioritizing tasks but often need help to effectively order tasks and manage workload.
levelDescriptions.2: You show improving skills in identifying more critical tasks and managing time more effectively, though occasionally may misalign priorities without guidance.
levelDescriptions.3: You consistently identify and focus on high-priority tasks, efficiently managing time and resources to meet strategic objectives without oversight.
levelDescriptions.4: You coach others in effective prioritization techniques, enhancing the team's ability to focus on key objectives and manage time efficiently.
levelDescriptions.5: You shape Curacel's approach to prioritization, developing systems and frameworks that ensure organizational focus on strategic goals and efficient resource allocation.

SubCompetency.name: Optimism
SubCompetency.description: You maintain a consistently positive outlook, even in the face of setbacks or uncertainty, believing that there is always a path forward. This means looking at every situation with the confidence that it can be overcome, and that every challenge is an opportunity for growth and improvement and it serves as a driving force for your team when they're dispirited.

levelDescriptions.1: You display a general sense of hope but may be easily swayed by challenges or setbacks, requiring support to maintain a positive outlook.
levelDescriptions.2: You maintain a positive attitude in familiar situations and is beginning to apply an optimistic outlook to overcome obstacles, with some encouragement.
levelDescriptions.3: You consistently exhibit a positive, optimistic mindset, using it as a driving force to navigate challenges and inspire others.
levelDescriptions.4: You actively spread optimism within the team, uplifting colleagues and contributing to a positive, can-do culture.
levelDescriptions.5: You instill a deeply rooted sense of optimism across Curacel, leading initiatives that build resilience and a positive outlook as core organizational values.

SubCompetency.name: Solution-Orientation
SubCompetency.description: You always look for solutions and opportunities not just for yourself or your team but also for the business instead of focusing on limitations or making excuses. This means actively encouraging your team to adopt a can-do attitude, fostering a culture where challenges are enthusiastically accepted and approached with a solution-oriented mindset.

levelDescriptions.1: You recognize problems and is open to solutions but often rely on others to provide answers or direction.
levelDescriptions.2: You actively seek solutions within a known framework and is becoming more adept at solving problems with occasional guidance.
levelDescriptions.3: You independently find creative and effective solutions to challenges, consistently applying a solution-oriented approach to work.
levelDescriptions.4: You guide others in identifying and implementing solutions, enhancing the team's problem-solving capabilities and creativity.
levelDescriptions.5: You shape the problem-solving culture at Curacel, developing and promoting methodologies that encourage innovative and effective solutions across the organization.

SubCompetency.name: Persistence
SubCompetency.description: You embody the perseverance to pursue goals and visions relentlessly, coupled with the flexibility to adapt strategies as needed. This means not only being persistent in the face of challenges but also being willing to adjust approaches based on new insights or changing circumstances, ensuring that optimism and solution-orientation are effectively channeled towards achieving Curacel's objectives.

levelDescriptions.1: You show initial determination in the face of obstacles but may quickly resort to seeking external help when faced with challenges.
levelDescriptions.2: You demonstrate increased resilience and continue efforts to overcome difficulties with some support, showing growing perseverance.
levelDescriptions.3: You display strong persistence in pursuing goals, adapting strategies as needed while maintaining focus and motivation through challenges.
levelDescriptions.4: You inspire and support others in their persistence, sharing strategies for resilience and adaptability in the face of adversity.
levelDescriptions.5: You lead by example and foster an environment where adaptive persistence is valued and encouraged, ensuring that Curacel's team members are equipped to persistently pursue and achieve their goals, even in changing circumstances.

levelDescriptions.1: Can build basic UI components with guidance.
levelDescriptions.2: Can develop simple user interfaces using Vue or React Native with support.
levelDescriptions.3: Can independently implement complex UIs and handle API integration and state management.
levelDescriptions.4: Can optimize frontend performance and lead UI component architecture across projects.
levelDescriptions.5: Can architect frontend frameworks and coach others in frontend best practices.

levelDescriptions.1: Can follow backend development patterns and build simple endpoints with assistance.
levelDescriptions.2: Can implement CRUD APIs and follow Laravel conventions independently.
levelDescriptions.3: Can design scalable services using Laravel, with good separation of concerns and DDD alignment.
levelDescriptions.4: Can lead service layer design, resolve architectural debt, and enforce backend coding standards.
levelDescriptions.5: Can define backend frameworks, mentor others, and drive backend architecture decisions across teams.

levelDescriptions.1: Can write basic queries and understand database tables with guidance.
levelDescriptions.2: Can model schemas and perform basic joins and indexing with supervision.
levelDescriptions.3: Can design normalized databases, write optimized queries, and manage migrations.
levelDescriptions.4: Can identify performance bottlenecks and tune database interactions for scale.
levelDescriptions.5: Can lead data modeling, partitioning, and storage design for complex, high-throughput systems.

levelDescriptions.1: Can consume a simple external API with help.
levelDescriptions.2: Can connect to and send data to 3rd-party systems using standard patterns.
levelDescriptions.3: Can build and maintain robust 3rd-party integrations, including auth and retries.
levelDescriptions.4: Can design integration frameworks and proactively manage external system dependencies.
levelDescriptions.5: Can architect scalable integration strategies, interface with enterprise platforms, and abstract integration logic.

levelDescriptions.1: Can write basic, functional code that runs, with help on structure.
levelDescriptions.2: Can follow code guidelines and apply basic formatting and linting.
levelDescriptions.3: Can write clean, testable code and provide constructive peer reviews.
levelDescriptions.4: Can enforce high code quality standards across modules and guide junior engineers.
levelDescriptions.5: Can define team-wide coding standards, automate quality enforcement, and lead refactoring efforts

levelDescriptions.1: Can push code to a repo and run a local app with support.
levelDescriptions.2: Can use existing CI/CD pipelines to deploy changes.
levelDescriptions.3: Can configure and troubleshoot CI/CD workflows for test and deployment automation.
levelDescriptions.4: Can optimize pipelines for speed, reliability, and rollback safety.
levelDescriptions.5: Can lead CI/CD strategy across teams and integrate delivery into larger platform engineering goals.

levelDescriptions.1: Can run Docker containers locally using documented commands.
levelDescriptions.2: Can build Docker images and deploy simple services in containers.
levelDescriptions.3: Can write Dockerfiles, manage local environments, and troubleshoot containerized services.
levelDescriptions.4: Can deploy and manage containerized apps on Kubernetes clusters.
levelDescriptions.5: Can define container orchestration strategy and mentor others in container best practices.

levelDescriptions.1: Can observe logs and alerts when guided but cannot yet identify root causes.
levelDescriptions.2: Can use logs and basic tools to diagnose minor production issues.
levelDescriptions.3: Can independently debug production issues and identify system bottlenecks.
levelDescriptions.4: Can implement observability tools (e.g., monitoring, tracing, alerting) and resolve complex outages.
levelDescriptions.5: Can design observability systems and lead postmortems, root cause analysis, and resilience strategy.

levelDescriptions.1: Can deploy to dev/staging but depends on others for production releases.
levelDescriptions.2: Can deploy low-risk updates with supervision and run sanity checks.
levelDescriptions.3: Can deploy features safely with rollback plans, health checks, and migration awareness.
levelDescriptions.4: Can coordinate and execute zero-downtime rollouts for major releases.
levelDescriptions.5: Can define company-wide deployment best practices and governance.

levelDescriptions.1: Can follow naming and modularity conventions but lacks understanding of domains.
levelDescriptions.2: Can structure code using basic domain logic boundaries with guidance.
levelDescriptions.3: Can apply DDD patterns (e.g., entities, services, value objects) to new features.
levelDescriptions.4: Can drive DDD adoption across modules and resolve domain overlap.
levelDescriptions.5: Can design entire systems around bounded contexts and coach others in DDD modeling.

levelDescriptions.1: Can write features that work but may not scale or remain maintainable.
levelDescriptions.2: Can write modular code and consider some edge cases for scale.
levelDescriptions.3: Can design components that are extensible, DRY, and resilient under load.
levelDescriptions.4: Can refactor systems for long-term maintainability and performance.
levelDescriptions.5: Can design platform-wide solutions that balance tech debt, growth, and maintainability.

levelDescriptions.1: Can write tests after development with help.
levelDescriptions.2: Can write basic unit tests and use assertions correctly.
levelDescriptions.3: Can use TDD as a core development practice across features.
levelDescriptions.4: Can enforce test coverage policies and write integration and E2E tests.
levelDescriptions.5: Can define automated testing strategy and train others in quality-first engineering.

levelDescriptions.1: Can follow security guidelines (e.g., password hashing) when instructed.
levelDescriptions.2: Can apply basic input validation, auth, and access control.
levelDescriptions.3: Can design secure endpoints and handle sensitive data appropriately.
levelDescriptions.4: Can identify security risks and lead mitigations or audits.
levelDescriptions.5: Can drive security architecture, threat modeling, and compliance across the stack.

levelDescriptions.1: Can answer basic questions from teammates when prompted.
levelDescriptions.2: Can support junior engineers through code reviews and pair programming.
levelDescriptions.3: Can mentor mid-level engineers and lead feature teams.
levelDescriptions.4: Can coach engineers on architecture, design, and delivery excellence.
levelDescriptions.5: Can build and lead engineering culture, leveling systems, and onboarding paths.

levelDescriptions.1: Can join design discussions but provides limited input.
levelDescriptions.2: Can give structured feedback in reviews and propose small improvements.
levelDescriptions.3: Can actively contribute to design sessions and architectural reviews.
levelDescriptions.4: Can lead design reviews and resolve architectural disagreements.
levelDescriptions.5: Can define design review frameworks and mentor teams on scalable decision-making.

levelDescriptions.1: Can complete assigned tasks on time but needs help prioritizing.
levelDescriptions.2: Can manage small modules or bugs with limited supervision.
levelDescriptions.3: Can lead end-to-end delivery of key features or components.
levelDescriptions.4: Can drive large initiatives and unblock others with little oversight.
levelDescriptions.5: Can own high-impact projects, align with business goals, and influence company roadmap.

levelDescriptions.1: Can document basic tasks or setup steps when asked.
levelDescriptions.2: Can write usage docs or how-tos for components with guidance.
levelDescriptions.3: Can document systems, decisions, and interfaces clearly for others.
levelDescriptions.4: Can institutionalize team documentation practices and conduct knowledge sessions.
levelDescriptions.5: Can lead knowledge systems and build a culture of transparency and documentation.

levelDescriptions.1: Can launch basic AWS services (e.g., EC2, S3) with supervision.
levelDescriptions.2: Can configure services like RDS, IAM, and Lambda with some guidance.
levelDescriptions.3: Can independently architect and manage AWS environments using best practices.
levelDescriptions.4: Can optimize, secure, and scale AWS infrastructure across environments.
levelDescriptions.5: Can lead cloud strategy, cost governance, and advanced multi-account AWS architecture.

levelDescriptions.1: Can navigate the GCP UI and deploy resources from templates.
levelDescriptions.2: Can replicate basic AWS setups in GCP and use core services like GCS or Cloud Run.
levelDescriptions.3: Can manage hybrid cloud workloads and support CI/CD across both platforms.
levelDescriptions.4: Can architect GCP-native infrastructure and advise on vendor-neutral deployments.
levelDescriptions.5: Can lead cloud abstraction initiatives and drive multi-cloud resilience strategies.

levelDescriptions.1: Can define security groups and IAM roles with support.
levelDescriptions.2: Can manage VPCs, subnets, route tables, and enforce IAM policies.
levelDescriptions.3: Can implement secure networking, role-based access control, and encryption at rest/in-transit.
levelDescriptions.4: Can design zero-trust network policies, rotate credentials, and monitor audit trails.
levelDescriptions.5: Can lead cloud security reviews, design defense-in-depth architectures, and ensure regulatory compliance.

levelDescriptions.1: Can deploy serverless functions with templates.
levelDescriptions.2: Can configure environments and test basic functions.
levelDescriptions.3: Can manage scalable serverless APIs and functions using Vapor or alternatives.
levelDescriptions.4: Can optimize cold starts, observability, and vendor limits in serverless deployments.
levelDescriptions.5: Can lead adoption of serverless architecture, governance, and cost modeling.

levelDescriptions.1: Can trigger basic pipelines and inspect logs with guidance.
levelDescriptions.2: Can modify simple pipelines and add build/test steps.
levelDescriptions.3: Can build CI/CD pipelines with branching, caching, and rollback logic.
levelDescriptions.4: Can optimize parallelism, deploy safely to production, and enforce policies.
levelDescriptions.5: Can define pipeline architecture standards and manage CI/CD reliability at scale.

levelDescriptions.1: Can recognize common CI/CD tools like Jenkins or GitHub Actions.
levelDescriptions.2: Can modify pipelines in different platforms with support.
levelDescriptions.3: Can translate pipeline logic between platforms effectively.
levelDescriptions.4: Can evaluate CI/CD platforms for use cases and performance.
levelDescriptions.5: Can drive platform migration, standardization, and organization-wide adoption.

levelDescriptions.1: Can deploy to staging and notify team for production promotion.
levelDescriptions.2: Can manage basic blue/green or canary deployments manually.
levelDescriptions.3: Can automate progressive rollouts with monitoring and rollback triggers.
levelDescriptions.4: Can coordinate high-availability releases with no downtime.
levelDescriptions.5: Can design platform-level deployment frameworks with SLA guarantees.

levelDescriptions.1: Can store and retrieve artifacts manually.
levelDescriptions.2: Can use tagging/versioning for consistent deployments.
levelDescriptions.3: Can manage artifact lifecycle, caching, and secure storage.
levelDescriptions.4: Can automate artifact promotion between environments.
levelDescriptions.5: Can design centralized artifact governance and traceability practices.

levelDescriptions.1: Can read existing IaC templates.
levelDescriptions.2: Can provision basic infrastructure from templates.
levelDescriptions.3: Can write reusable, modular infrastructure definitions with state management.
levelDescriptions.4: Can design IaC frameworks and enforce drift detection and plan validation.
levelDescriptions.5: Can lead cross-project infrastructure standardization and policy as code adoption.

levelDescriptions.1: Can write basic shell scripts to automate repeat tasks.
levelDescriptions.2: Can create scripts for provisioning, log rotation, or service monitoring.
levelDescriptions.3: Can build secure, idempotent scripts for production workflows.
levelDescriptions.4: Can refactor scripts into reusable libraries and integrate into pipelines.
levelDescriptions.5: Can architect automation ecosystems with service orchestration logic.

levelDescriptions.1: Can manually apply system configurations.
levelDescriptions.2: Can use scripts to apply common settings.
levelDescriptions.3: Can standardize configurations across environments with templates.
levelDescriptions.4: Can enforce compliance through automation and monitoring.
levelDescriptions.5: Can define and manage configuration governance across products.

levelDescriptions.1: Can follow basic OS setup steps securely.
levelDescriptions.2: Can automate system setup using scripts.

levelDescriptions.5: Is able to set the strategic direction for the organizationâ€™s wellbeing initiatives, forecasting future needs and trends and collaborates with various stakeholders to ensure the offerings are comprehensive and inclusive.

levelDescriptions.1: Is able to understand that organizational structure and the physical work environment can impact employee wellbeing.
levelDescriptions.2: Is able to engage more deeply with some supervision how various aspects of organizational design, like team configurations, communication flows, and decision-making processes, influence employee morale and mental health.
levelDescriptions.3: Is actively involved in recommending and implementing design changes that enhance wellbeing. This might include redesigning job roles to reduce ambiguity and stress.
levelDescriptions.4: Can align organizational design with wellbeing initiatives, ensuring that the entire structural setup of the organization promotes a healthy work environment.
levelDescriptions.5: Can lead transformative changes in organizational design that could serve as models within the industry for promoting employee wellbeing.

levelDescriptions.1: Can understand that a diverse and inclusive environment can significantly enhance employee wellbeing but is not yet fully involved in decisions or initiatives that can achieve it.
levelDescriptions.2: Is able understand specific challenges faced by diverse groups within the workplace and with some level of supervision can explore how inclusive practices can address these challenges to improve overall workplace health.
levelDescriptions.3: Can ensure that wellbeing programs are accessible to all employees, tailored to meet the varied needs of a diverse workforce and monitors and adjusts programs based on feedback to enhance their effectiveness.
levelDescriptions.4: Can design and implement comprehensive strategies that address systemic inequalities impacting employee wellbeing.
levelDescriptions.5: Can drive organisational and industry-wide changes and advocates for policies that enhance wellbeing through increased diversity and inclusion.

levelDescriptions.1: Is able to recognize the types of wellbeing benefits typically offered by organizations, such as health insurance, mental health programs, and fitness memberships. Understands the basic role these benefits play in supporting employee health and satisfaction.
levelDescriptions.2: Is able to begin engaging with the processes of selecting and managing wellbeing benefits, taking into account employee feedback and industry trends with supervision.
levelDescriptions.3: Is able to balance the value and benefits of wellbeing (tangible and intangible) with business needs.
levelDescriptions.4: Can integrate wellbeing benefits into the broader human resources strategy to enhance employee engagement and organizational performance.
levelDescriptions.5: Can lead the organization in setting standards for employee wellbeing benefits that are recognized industry-wide and how to balance the value of wellbeing with business strategy.

SubCompetency.name: Identifying & monitoring wellbeing trends with data

levelDescriptions.1: Can understand the fundamental importance of data in tracking and assessing wellbeing trends, paying attention to what data and qualitative information are effective in identifying and monitoring wellbeing trends.
levelDescriptions.2: Can monitor wellbeing trends through data and qualitative information, and evaluate outcomes of wellbeing solutions to make connections between data findings and potential impacts on workplace wellbeing with supervision.
levelDescriptions.3: Is able to skillfully analyze and interpret wellbeing data, using more sophisticated tools and methodologies to enable change which supports better wellbeing.
levelDescriptions.4: Can design targeted interventions based on predictive analysis and trend monitoring to proactively address potential wellbeing issues before they escalate and continuously drive business strategy.
levelDescriptions.5: Is able to champion the use of innovative data practices to continuously predict & improve wellbeing outcomes.

levelDescriptions.1: Is familiar with the importance of considering individual differences, approaches and preferences in the delivery of wellbeing services but involvement is minimal.
